<subSubSection id="40B26541FFA3EA046EE0D318FDCCFB1B" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1089" pageId="1" pageNumber="1087" type="description">
<paragraph id="081736CAFFA3EA046EE0D318FDCCFB1B" blockId="1.[707,1194,1230,1730]" lastBlockId="3.[173,660,193,1729]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1089" pageId="1" pageNumber="1087">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA3EA066EE0D318FCEEFAB6" bold="true" box="[731,853,1337,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1087">Description.</emphasis>
Length 3.0 mm from vertex of head to tip of elytra. 
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA3EA066F63D372FC2DFA90" bold="true" box="[856,918,1363,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1087">Head:</emphasis>
Ground color of integument black except anterior part of head, labrum, and mouthparts bright orange; mandible apically darkened (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA3EA066EC6D382FCFDFA40" box="[765,838,1443,1464]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[175,206,1656,1675]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-0@2.[164,1159,194,1640]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Brodskyella konvickai, holotype. A–B) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, exterior and interior views, I) Pygidium." pageId="1" pageNumber="1087">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
); covered by short, dense, recumbent setae. Eyes comparatively small (ocular index 54.9), reaching occiput (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA3EA066F4BD3F9FC00FA15" box="[880,955,1496,1517]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[175,206,1656,1675]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-0@2.[164,1159,194,1640]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Brodskyella konvickai, holotype. A–B) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, exterior and interior views, I) Pygidium." pageId="1" pageNumber="1087">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
), not extending onto the ventral surface of head, finely facetted. Maxillary palpi orange, apical palpomere securiform (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA3EA06686FD02CFB27F9DA" box="[1108,1180,1549,1570]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[175,206,1656,1675]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-0@2.[164,1159,194,1640]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Brodskyella konvickai, holotype. A–B) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, exterior and interior views, I) Pygidium." pageId="1" pageNumber="1087">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
); labial palpi orange, apical palpomere ellipsoidal. Mouthparts lacking any visible sexual dimorphism. Antennae moderately long; antennomeres 1–4 cylindrical; antennomere 1 2.5X longer than wide; antennomere 2 2.0X longer than wide; antennomeres 3–4 2.0X longer than wide; antennomeres 5–10 weakly serrate, 1.7X longer than wide; antennomere 11 ellipsoidal, 1.9X longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046C8FD6D6FEBBFEF4" box="[180,256,247,268]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[175,206,1656,1675]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-0@2.[164,1159,194,1640]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Brodskyella konvickai, holotype. A–B) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, exterior and interior views, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
); antennomeres 1–5 bright orange, 6–11 darkened. 
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046D34D730FEDAFEDE" bold="true" box="[271,353,273,294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Thorax:</emphasis>
Elytra long and slender, 2.9X as long as wide across humeral calli; ground color of integument orange, becoming dark brown towards elytral margins, suture, and apex. Elytra entirely covered by short, recumbent, posteriorly oriented, black setae (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046D1ED7B7FEC9FE53" box="[293,370,406,427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[175,206,1656,1675]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-0@2.[164,1159,194,1640]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Brodskyella konvickai, holotype. A–B) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, exterior and interior views, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Ground color of integument of pronotum black, entirely covered by posteriorly oriented, yellowish pubescence; pubescence longer and less dense than on head. Pronotum as long as wide in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046DBAD421FE70FDED" box="[385,459,512,533]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[175,206,1656,1675]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-0@2.[164,1159,194,1640]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Brodskyella konvickai, holotype. A–B) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, exterior and interior views, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
); anterior margin of pronotum margined, gently curved from median anterior lobe to anterior angles (not visible from above); lateral margin gradually curved from anterior to posterior angles; posterior margin emarginate, posterior median lobe protruding backwards; posterior angles rectangular in dorsal aspect. Ventral side of meso- and metathoraces black, covered by sparse, light yellowish pubescence (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046E33D4F4FDEFFD12" box="[520,596,725,746]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[175,206,1656,1675]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-0@2.[164,1159,194,1640]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Brodskyella konvickai, holotype. A–B) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, exterior and interior views, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Scutellum triangular, black. 
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046D91D4D1FE5AFCFD" bold="true" box="[426,481,752,773]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Legs:</emphasis>
Fore legs bright orange; middle legs reddish brown, becoming paler distally; hind legs dark reddish brown (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046E24D504FD33FCC2" box="[543,648,804,826]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[175,206,1656,1675]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-0@2.[164,1159,194,1640]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Brodskyella konvickai, holotype. A–B) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, exterior and interior views, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 1G–H</figureCitation>
). Protibia straight, only feebly curved; protarsus elongated, 1.4X longer than protibia. Mesotibia straight; mesotarsus 1.2X longer than mesotibia. Metatibia with 1 apical ridge and 2 oblique lateral ridges. Metatarsomere 1 with 2 ridges, metatarsomeres 2 and 3 each with 1 ridge. Metatibial spurs subequal in length, yellow (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046D76D5FEFE25FC0C" box="[333,414,991,1012]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[175,206,1656,1675]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-0@2.[164,1159,194,1640]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Brodskyella konvickai, holotype. A–B) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, exterior and interior views, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046D8CD5FEFDA5FC0C" bold="true" box="[439,542,991,1012]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Pygidium:</emphasis>
Conical in dorsal view, 2.7X as long as wide at base, 1.3X as long as hypopygidium (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046DA2D235FE67FBD1" box="[409,476,1044,1065]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[175,206,1656,1675]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-0@2.[164,1159,194,1640]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Brodskyella konvickai, holotype. A–B) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, exterior and interior views, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046DC8D235FDE3FBD1" bold="true" box="[499,600,1044,1065]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Genitalia:</emphasis>
Parameres asymmetrical (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046DB2D20FFE66FBBB" box="[393,477,1070,1091]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[197,228,684,703]" captionTargetBox="[176,1188,198,666]" captionTargetId="figure-458@5.[175,1190,194,669]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Brodskyella species, parameres. A) B. konvickai, B) B. viraktmathi, C) B. angustata, D) B. holzschuhi. Illustrations C and B from Horák (1989)." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Right paramere U-shaped; dorsal branch apically expanded and rounded; ventral branch apically narrowed and pointed, dorsally bent. Left paramere lacking ventral branch; dorsal branch apically expanded and rounded, covered by setae; medial process apically expanded, ventrally produced, truncate at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="5CD76642FFA0EA056C94D059FDFEF943" pageId="2" pageNumber="1088" startId="2.[175,206,1656,1675]" targetBox="[166,1157,196,1638]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="081736CAFFA0EA056C94D059FDFEF943" blockId="2.[151,1172,1655,1723]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1088">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA0EA056C94D059FF50F973" bold="true" box="[175,235,1656,1675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1088">Fig. 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA0EA056D3BD056FE06F972" box="[256,445,1655,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1088" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="konvickai">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA0EA056D3BD056FE06F972" box="[256,445,1655,1674]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1088">Brodskyella konvickai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, holotype. A–B) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, exterior and interior views, I) Pygidium.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="40B26541FFA1EA046CFED2C9FEC7FACA" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="081736CAFFA1EA046CFED2C9FEC7FACA" blockId="3.[173,660,193,1729]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046CFED2C9FE8CFB05" bold="true" box="[197,311,1256,1277]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species in named after Ondřej Konvička, our esteemed friend and specialist on the family 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA1EA046CC9D33CFEC2FACA" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[242,377,1309,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Melandryidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="40B26541FFA1EA046CFED319FCA7FF09" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="081736CAFFA1EA046CFED319FCA7FF09" blockId="3.[173,660,193,1729]" lastBlockId="3.[707,1193,194,241]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046CFED319FE97FAB5" bold="true" box="[197,300,1336,1357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA1EA046D07D316FDACFAB5" box="[316,535,1335,1357]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="konvickai">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046D07D316FDACFAB5" box="[316,535,1335,1357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Brodskyella konvickai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA1EA046D3FD372FE3AFA90" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[260,385,1363,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustata">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046D3FD372FE3AFA90" box="[260,385,1363,1384]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">B. angustata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance, but 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA1EA046C96D34CFE9DFA7A" box="[173,294,1388,1410]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="konvickai">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046C96D34CFE9DFA7A" box="[173,294,1388,1410]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">B. konvickai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the latter in having the dorsal part of the head capsule almost completely black with a transverse orange band between the antennal insertions (entire anterior half of head capsule and lateral parts along the eyes orange in 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA1EA046C96D3D3FE92F9FF" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[173,297,1522,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustata">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046C96D3D3FE92F9FF" box="[173,297,1522,1543]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">B. angustata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). These two species can be reliably separated only by the shape of the parameres (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046C88D006FEA3F9C4" box="[179,280,1575,1597]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[197,228,684,703]" captionTargetBox="[176,1188,198,666]" captionTargetId="figure-458@5.[175,1190,194,669]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Brodskyella species, parameres. A) B. konvickai, B) B. viraktmathi, C) B. angustata, D) B. holzschuhi. Illustrations C and B from Horák (1989)." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 3A–C</figureCitation>
): the ventral branch of the right paramere in 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA1EA046CFDD063FE8EF9AF" box="[198,309,1601,1623]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="konvicka">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046CFDD063FE8EF9AF" box="[198,309,1601,1623]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">B. konvicka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is strongly curved, almost falciform, while in 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA1EA046D32D07DFE3FF989" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[265,388,1628,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustata">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046D32D07DFE3FF989" box="[265,388,1628,1649]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">B. angustata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this branch in only feebly hooked. From 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA1EA046D04D056FE7AF974" authorityName="Horak" authorityYear="1989" box="[319,449,1654,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holzschuhi">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046D04D056FE7AF974" box="[319,449,1654,1676]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">B. holzschuhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA1EA046DC3D057FDBCF95E" authority="Ruzzier and Yeshwanth" authorityName="Ruzzier and Yeshwanth" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viraktamathi" status="new species">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046DC3D057FEB5F95F" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Brodskyella viraktamathi</emphasis>
Ruzzier and Yeshwanth
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21EF57A3FFA1EA046E2CD0B0FD2BF95E" box="[535,656,1681,1702]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA1EA046C96D08DFE98F939" box="[173,291,1707,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="konvickai">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046C96D08DFE98F939" box="[173,291,1707,1729]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">B. konvickai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having the entire pronotum black instead of orange only in the anterior portions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
